ur results reveal that all the studied configurations\nassociated with the halogen defects do not derive in metallic states nor extra\npolarons that would increase considerably the electronic conductivity. This is\nmainly due to the ionic characteristics of the Li$_{2}$O$_{2}$ crystal and the\ncapability of the oxygen dimers to adapt its valence rather than to the nature\nof the dopant itself.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 May 2018 18:45:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-11"}
