o model on small-world graphs, in addition to the\ntransition to synchronization, we identify a new bifurcation leading to stable\nrandom twisted states. The examples analyzed in this work complement the\nresults in [Chiba, Medvedev, The mean field analysis for the Kuramoto model on\ngraphs (parts I and II), arxiv].\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 May 2018 02:20:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-15"}
